MO DUK PAI
JULY 19, 1979

Technical Letter #10
HAND COMBINATIONS

NOTE: Do all hand combinations from a tiger stance. Shuffle straight in unless
otherwise noted. Keep center line covered. (R) = right; (L) = left.

#1 (R) reverse backfist hooking to (L) temple. (L) hand protecting face. (L)
poke to eyes, (R) hand on outside of (L) elbow. (R) backfist to (L) temple. (L)
vertical punch to sternum. (R) horizontal chop to windpipe. (L) backfist to
cheek.

#2 Step (R) left 45 degrees right. (R) vertical returning backfist to face. (L)
poke to eyes, simultaneously moving into (R) tiger. (R) backfist to groin. (L)
vertical punch to solar plexus. (R) horizontal chop to windpipe or snake
(finger whip) to eyes.

#3 (L) open hand soft outward block to radial nerve with (R) tiger claw to face,
simultaneously stepping in with (R) tiger. (L) palm strike to sternum with (R)
slap to groin with back of hand (i.e. fingers). (R) hand circles up and tears
(L) ear, coming downward and across your body. (L) hand by your face, grabs,
tearing opponent's face. (R) hand snapping with tiger claw to (R) ear.

#4 Person cocks and you attack with (R) vertical chop to (R) shoulder joint. (R)
vertical chop to (L) shoulder joint. (L) vertical chop to sternum. (R)
horizontal chop to cheek.

#5 Simultaneous (L) open hand soft inward block and (R) back hand to groin
(stepping into tiger). Then (L) circle backfist (striking downward with a short
circle at elbow, ripping and spinning to backfist) to sternum. (R) horizontal
chop to throat or snake to eyes.

#6 Simultaneous (L) open hand soft outward block and (R) poke to throat, eye,
and ear. (L) elbow strike to strenum, simultaneously stepping in to (R) tiger.
(L) downward chop to neck (following chop, left hand continues
downward--blocking in peacock--ending by side of your ribs). (R) chop to neck
immediately follows, ending in (R) cat stance.

#7 Straight punch: Simultaneously stepping to (L) 90 degree angle and outside
split block (left palm heel to ribs and right split block), flipping (R) hand
over simultaneously poking eyes with (R), step through to (R) tiger. (L)
peacock strike to groin. (R) elbow to face. (R) backfist.

#8 Double roundhouse punch: Simultaneous (L) open hand soft outward block and
(R) vertical chop to strenum. Then (R) open hand soft outward block and (L)
poke to eyes. (R) chop downward (across neck and throat), bend at torso. (R)
back fist to groin. (L) vertical punch to solar plexus. (R) snake to eyes or
ear.

#9 Upward punch: Simultaneous (L) brush block, then (R) poke to eyes (your arm
on outside of opponent's arm). Grab with (R) hand (slide down arm to wrist) and
pull. (L) vertical punch to head. (R) elbow smash follow up.

Love, Sifu

Frederic D. King Founder

